21/09/2004
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The country's State Investigation and Protection Agency will begin participating in the detention of war crimes indictees. The decision was announced after a meeting between High Representative Paddy Ashdown, BiH Security Minister Barisa Colak and EU Police Mission Commissioner Kevin Carty on Monday (20 September). 
In other news Monday, BiH Prime Minister Adnan Terzic met with Norwegian Parliament Speaker Jorgen Kosmo, who expressed support for government efforts to bring the country into Euro-Atlantic structures. Kosmo and Terzic agreed that BiH's accession to NATO's Partnership for Peace programme would encourage foreign investment. (Dnevni avaz - 21/09/04; Fena, Pincom.info, PBS BiH - 20/09/04) 
